2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
113 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Gala Apple
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
56 g Carrot, julienned
2 tbsp Tahini Sauce
9 g Sesame Seeds
2 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 tbsp Soy Sauce
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 tbsp Moo Shu Spice Blend
28 g Almonds, sliced
1.5 tbsp Oil*
2 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Heat medium pot over medium-high heat.
When hot, add almonds to the dry pot. Toast, stirring often, until golden, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn.)
Transfer to a plate.

Add carrots, vinegar,1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water and 2 tsp (4 tsp) sugar to the same pot used to toast almonds. Season with salt. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat. Once simmering, cook, stirring often, until sugar dissolves, 1-2 min.
Remove from heat. Transfer carrots, including liquid, to a large bowl. Set aside in the fridge to cool

Thinly slice cucumber.
Core, then coarsely grate half the apple. Thinly slice remaining.

Add panko, grated apple, Moo Shu Spice Blend, sesame seeds and soy sauce to a large bowl. Stir to combine.
Add Beyond Meat® patties to panko mixture. Season with salt and pepper, then combine.
Form mixture into 6 (12 for 4 ppl) 2-inch-wide patties.

Heat a medium non-stick pan over medium-high heat (large pan for 4 ppl).
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties.
Reduce heat to medium. Cook, flipping halfway until patties are golden and cooked through, 5-8 min.**
While patties cook, drain all but 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) pickling liquid from carrots. Add half the tahini sauce and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Stir to mix.

Add cucumber, spring mix, almonds and remaining apple to bowl of dressing. Toss to coat.
Divide salad and Beyond Meat® patties between plates.
Drizzle remaining tahini sauce over patties.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, prepare and cook it the same way the recipe instructs you to prepare and cook the turkey.**